#compdef ladylua ll
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LadyLua — single executable, static, batteries-included Lua 5.1 interpreter
#           (Go, 86★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/tongson/LadyLua
# author : Allan Crisostomo (tongson) — long-time Lua + Go practitioner
# license: MIT
# binary : `ll`  (installed as the `ll` binary — completion also fires
#          for `ladylua` for users who alias the longer name).  Note that
#          most shells alias `ll` to `ls -l`; that alias is expanded before
#          completion fires, so this completion only activates when the
#          user invokes the actual LadyLua binary directly (e.g. via
#          `\ll`, `command ll`, or after `unalias ll`).
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from cmd/ll/main.go
# `flag.StringVar` / `flag.IntVar` / `flag.BoolVar` registrations + the
# `flag.Usage` help block on the LadyLua v0.11.0 "Tarot Cruncher" tip.
#
# Direct deps from go.mod (selected — LadyLua is the rare Go CLI that
# bundles gopher-lua as a NON-INDIRECT first-class dep):
#   github.com/yuin/gopher-lua    ← canonical Go Lua interpreter
#                                   (this axis) — by Yusuke Inuzuka
#                                   (yuin), pure-Go Lua 5.1 implementation
#                                   with full coroutine support, GoString
#                                   / GoFunc interop, and a State-per-
#                                   goroutine concurrency model.  Replaced
#                                   in LadyLua's `replace` directive with
#                                   tongson's own fork to expose extra
#                                   internals.
#   github.com/yuin/gluamapper    (struct↔Lua-table marshalling)
#   github.com/chzyer/readline    (the readline lib also used by rhai-repl
#                                  on Rust=224, with vi/emacs bindings)
#   github.com/oklog/ulid/v2      (axis 168 callback — LadyLua exposes ULID
#                                  generation as a `ulid` Lua module)
#   github.com/segmentio/ksuid    (K-sortable IDs from Segment.com — also
#                                  ULID-family identifier)
#   github.com/go-redis/redis/v8
#   github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql
#   github.com/go-telegram-bot-api/telegram-bot-api
#   github.com/slack-go/slack
#   github.com/gregdel/pushover
#   github.com/pelletier/go-toml
#   github.com/ghodss/yaml
#   github.com/pierrec/lz4
#   github.com/rs/zerolog
#   github.com/hashicorp/go-uuid
#   github.com/fsnotify/fsnotify
#   git.mills.io/prologic/bitcask  (embedded log-structured KV)
#   github.com/kevinburke/ssh_config
#
# LadyLua ships every batteries-included Lua module pre-loaded into the
# interpreter at startup: `fs`, `os`, `extend`, `exec` (globals) + `http`,
# `json`, `crypto`, `ksuid`, `mysql`, `lz4`, `telegram`, `pushover`,
# `slack`, `logger`, `fsnotify`, `bitcask`, `refmt`, `uuid`, `ulid`,
# `redis`, `ssh_config`, `socket_core`, `socket_except`, `socket` (via
# `require`).  Resulting binary is ~30MB static and runs identically
# anywhere a Linux/macOS/Windows binary runs — making it the canonical
# answer to "I want Lua + a network/JSON/Redis/SQL library without
# installing LuaRocks + libc Lua + C compiler toolchain on the box."
#
# === AXIS 169 CONTINUES — embedded scripting languages ecosystem ========
# Axis position: Go=224 continues Axis 169 (slot 2/0/0).  Canonical Go
# embedded scripting language is `github.com/yuin/gopher-lua` by Yusuke
# Inuzuka — pure-Go Lua 5.1 interpreter that integrates cleanly with Go's
# goroutine model (one `*lua.LState` per goroutine, no shared interpreter
# state).  Used by every Go project that needs user-extensible behavior:
# honeytrap honeypot framework, gostatsd custom telemetry transforms,
# go-ycsb workload scripts, LadyLua's batteries-included interpreter.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=224    _rhai-run / _rhai-repl / _rhai-dbg  ← previous (axis 169
#                                                    OPENS at slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=224      ← THIS FILE              (axis 169 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=224 ← next round              (axis 169 CLOSES at triple-224, 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_ladylua() {
    _arguments -s \
        '-e=[execute string `stat`]:Lua statement:' \
        '-l=[require library `name`]:library name:' \
        '-mx=[memory limit in MB (default unlimited)]:megabytes:' \
        '-dt[dump AST trees (parse output via github.com/yuin/gopher-lua/parse)]' \
        '-dc[dump VM codes (bytecode disassembly)]' \
        '-i[enter interactive readline mode after executing `script` (via chzyer/readline)]' \
        '-p=[write CPU profiles to the file (runtime/pprof.StartCPUProfile)]:profile output file:_files' \
        '-v[show version information (e.g. "0.11.0 Tarot Cruncher")]' \
        '*:Lua script (then args to the script):_files -g "*.lua"'
}

_ladylua "$@"
